Feature Scaling

Why we need Scaling?

  • Linear Regression

    • if we scale down our features then there is higher chance that our randomly selected coefficient will be near our optimal value.

  • KNN Neighbour

    • If we scale down the feature then the distance that our algorithm calculate will be small and hence algorithm will compute faster

When not necessary to use Scaling-

  • in ensemble type of Algorithm it is not necessary to scale down our features
    • Eg- Decision Tree, Random Forest, XGBoost

Standardization (Z-Score Normalization)-

X' = ( X - X̅ ) / sigma
 after using this formula what we will get is
 mean = 0 and 
 standard Deviation(Sigma) = 1

Normalization -

1. Min Max Scaling
2. Mean Normalization
3. Max Absolute Scaling
4. Robust Scaling

1.Min Max Scaling


  • Will get the result between [0, 1]

2.Mean Normalization


  • Will get the result between [-1, 1]

3.MaxAbsScaling


  • Usually used in Sparse Data (data which have many Zeros)

4.Robust Scaling


  • This performs best in dealing with outliners
